The paper discusses diffusion processes in networks, which are commonly studied in the fields of social networks and computational sustainability. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also presents optimization techniques for learning the underlying dynamics of contagion processes, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of aggregate information, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also presents empirical results, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). Finally, the paper discusses the spread of infectious diseases, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cs.SOC (Computational Social Science).
